The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, specifically for Human Epithelial Type-2 (HEp-2) cells staining patterns. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of cross-specimen analysis, which involves training on multiple specimens to improve generalization, indicating a potential focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
